*selinux-sources-2.4.24-r2 (18 Feb 2004)

  18 Feb 2004; <plasmaroo@gentoo.org> selinux-sources-2.4.24-r1.ebuild,
  selinux-sources-2.4.24-r2.ebuild, files/selinux-sources-2.4.24.munmap.patch:
  Added the patch for the mremap/munmap vulnerability. Bug #42024.

*selinux-sources-2.4.24-r1 (10 Jan 2004)

  10 Jan 2004; Chris PeBenito <pebenito@gentoo.org>
  selinux-sources-2.4.24-r1.ebuild:
  Fix mremap patch.

*selinux-sources-2.4.24 (05 Jan 2004)

  05 Jan 2004; Chris PeBenito <pebenito@gentoo.org>
  selinux-sources-2.4.24.ebuild:
  New kernel release to fix mremap vulnerability, and rtc kernel memory leak to
  userland. Otherwise same LSM/SELinux and xattr patches.

  03 Jan 2004; Chris PeBenito <pebenito@gentoo.org>
  selinux-sources-2.4.23.ebuild:
  Mark stable

*selinux-sources-2.4.23 (16 Dec 2003)

  16 Dec 2003; Chris PeBenito <pebenito@gentoo.org>
  selinux-sources-2.4.23.ebuild:
  New upstream version.

*selinux-sources-2.4.21-r5 (02 Dec 2003)

  02 Dec 2003; Brian Jackson <iggy@gentoo.org>
  selinux-sources-2.4.21-r5.ebuild:
  Version bump for 'do_brk' vulnerability.

  01 Dec 2003; Brian Jackson <iggy@gentoo.org>
  selinux-sources-2.4.21-r4.ebuild, files/do_brk_fix.patch:
  Fix 'do_brk' vulnerability.

  20 Nov 2003; Brandon Low <lostlogic@gentoo.org>
  selinux-sources-2.4.21-r4.ebuild:
  Move version handling logic to after inherit kernel, or insert it where
  necessary.

*selinux-sources-2.4.21-r4 (26 Oct 2003)

